g.text: In this example, MyBucketName is an output that shows the name of the S3 bucket after the stack is created
Outputs allow you to specify values you want to make visible after CloudFormation stack has been created or updated. This cloud be information like resource IDs, URLs or other
key details that are useful outside the stack. (Just like print statements)

Exports make the output of one stack available to other stacks. This is useful for sharing resources across stacks. You can use the Fn::ImportValue function to import an exported value into another stack.
Here, MyBucketExport is the name of the export that can be used by other stacks.
This imports the MyBucketExport value from the first stack.
Outputs help with debugging or getting key info about your stack.
Exports allow sharing resources like VPCs, subnet, or security groups across different CloudFormation stacks. (if you need to use same in other stack)
